# {{REPO_NAME}} Agent Dashboard

This optional dashboard is a human-readable operational view for the current
collaboration state. It is not the durable source of truth and does not grant
approval.

## Authority / COLLAB.md Wins

- `DASHBOARD.md` summarizes current state for fast human and agent orientation.
- `.agent-handoff/COLLAB.md` remains authoritative.
- On conflict, `COLLAB.md` wins.
- The detecting agent must reconcile this dashboard to `COLLAB.md` before using
  it for handoff when dashboard edits are in scope.
- If dashboard edits are out of scope, record the mismatch in the current turn
  note and in the Human Decision Packet / artifact visibility fields.

## Dashboard Freshness Timing

Start from this dashboard when it exists, then confirm against `COLLAB.md` and
the latest relevant turn notes before relying on it.

Refresh the dashboard before reliance if it is stale and dashboard edits are in
scope. Refresh again at handoff when any of these fields changed:

- next actor
- active role
- human-attention state
- artifact visibility
- latest artifact
- next safe action
- dashboard-vs-COLLAB conflict status
- What The Human Approver Pastes Next
- External Advisor Input
- Current Operational Nodes
- Subagent delegations

